\pard\pardeftab720

\b0\fs32 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Above all, remember that writing is a process that involves iteratively re-reading and redrafting as necessary. Allocate plenty of time for the write-up, plenty of time for your supervisor to provide feedback, and plenty of time for further revisions after that.  Allow several days for printing and binding; things don\'92t always go as planned.\
\
As mentioned above, the deadline for submitting 
\b \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
a first draft of your report is the end of Week 17
\b0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
. This implies that you should start planning your report and writing any parts that you can early in the Lent term. Giving your supervisor a draft before the final deadline gives you chance to incorporate the supervisor\'92s suggestions into the report and complete the final version in the remaining time.\
\
Once again: check your spellings and all cross-references very carefully. Finally, note that the \'93project\'94 encapsulates everything you do for the module: literature analysis, prototype development, evaluation, empirical study, the report, and any other you've done. So in your report, refer to parts of this work accurately, for example as the \'93system\'94 or the \'93empirical study\'94 (or similar), not as \'93the project\'94. If you\'92ve developed a new system, it can be good to come up with a short name or acronym for it so you can easily refer to it throughout your report.\
